We use \"Microsoft Teams\" for managing.message: We use "Microsoft Teams" for managing the community as it provides an easy way to stay connected. In order to join the community, you should click and register with Microsoft Teams: Microsoft Teams Invitation Form If you already have an account, just join the "Juka Programming Language" group. It's public and anyone can join!

Juka is built by the community, for the.message: Juka is built by the community, for the community. Please consider contributing to the Juka GitHub repository at

When you create new features, please fol.message: When you create new features, please follow the guidelines specified in the project documentation.

Juka is built on top of .NET framework..message: Juka is built on top of .NET framework. This means that Juka can run on many platforms including Windows, Linux, MacOS (coming soon), iOS/iPadOS (coming soon) and Android.

You can run Juka on Microsoft's Azure Se.message: You can run Juka on Microsoft's Azure Server by using Juka's built-in Azure Function.
